{
  "text": "The creeping bentgrass putting green containing the microplot study was clipped at a 4.0-mm height 6 days per week. The green was maintained using best management practices for irrigation, fertility, and fungal disease management as previously detailed by Settle et al. [CITATION_1] . Periodic sand top-dressing was used to compensate for soil settling in the microplots, which was greatest during the first year. Insecticides were not used during the study.",
  "citation_candidates": [
